benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/catalog/xml - Upload the full catalog as XML

covered: Valid Payload: Scenarios TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05, TC13, TC14, TC16, TC18, TC19, TC20, TC21, TC22, TC24, TC25, TC27, TC28, TC29, TC30, TC31 cover successful uploads with various header configurations, payload sizes, and content types.
Invalid Payloads: TC08, TC09, TC18, TC23, TC29 (malformed, empty, or corrupted XML), and security scenarios cover invalid or malicious content.
Header Validation: TC06, TC07, TC11, TC27 cover missing or extra headers, including minimal headers.
Edge Cases: TC12, TC13, TC24, TC25, TC27, TC28, TC29, TC30 cover large payloads, special characters, duplicate versions, comments, different encodings, boundary values.
Regression & Compatibility: TC21, TC22 test known bugs and backward compatibility.
Performance & Load: TC19, TC20 test under load and concurrency.
Authorization & Authentication: TC14, TC16 cover missing or invalid auth, backend down, service unavailability.
Additional Content & Security: TC17 tests malicious content, TC28 tests comments and CDATA, TC29 tests encodings.
Edge cases like whitespace-only payloads (TC23), duplicate versions (TC25), and boundary values (TC30) are included.
gaps: Authorization: No explicit tests for invalid or missing auth tokens beyond TC14.
Rate Limiting: No tests for request throttling or rate limiting.
Caching Behavior: No tests for cache headers like ETag or Cache-Control.
Network interruptions: No explicit tests simulating network failures during upload.
Partial/corrupted XML beyond TC18 could be expanded.
Specific tests for unsupported content types other than JSON or XML are limited.
No explicit tests for soft deletes or version conflict resolution beyond duplicate version handling.
recommendations: Add tests for authorization failures with invalid or missing tokens.
Implement rate limiting and throttling tests to verify system robustness under load.
Include scenarios verifying cache headers and caching behavior.
Simulate network failures during upload to test system resilience.
Expand partial/corrupted XML tests to cover more corruption scenarios.
Test unsupported content types beyond application/xml, such as application/json.
Add tests for version conflict resolution and soft delete behaviors if applicable.
